"title": "5518: seal",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5518",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A personalised design used to produce an imprint in clay or wax which was then attached, usually to documents and letters as a mark of ownership, authenticity and authority. A seal might also refer to what is given as a pledge or guarantee or be used to keep something secure.</p>\n<h2>The nature and use of a seal</h2>\n<h3>Seals engraved on precious stone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:11\">EXO 28:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:6\">EXO 39:6</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:21\">EXO 28:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:14\">EXO 39:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36\">EXO 28:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:30\">EXO 39:30</a></p>\n<h3>Seals used to imprint soft clay</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:14\">JOB 38:14</a></p>\n<h2>Ways of carrying a personal seal</h2>\n<h3>Figuratively used</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:6\">SNG 8:6</a></p>\n<h3>Worn round the neck</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:18\">GEN 38:18</a></strong> <em>The seal took the form of an engraved cylinder pierced from end to end and worn on a cord round the neck.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:25\">GEN 38:25</a></p>\n<h3>Worn as a signet ring</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:24\">JER 22:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:50\">NUM 31:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:21\">ISA 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>A seal as a mark of authority</h2>\n<h3>Given to signify delegation of authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:42\">GEN 41:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:10\">EST 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:2\">EST 8:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:2\">REV 7:2</a></p>\n<h3>God's seal validates his servants' ministry</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:27\">JHN 6:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:2\">1CO 9:2</a></p>\n<h3>A seal authenticates documents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:8-Esth8:10\">EST 8:8–8:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:8\">1KI 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:12\">EST 3:12</a></p>\n<h2>A seal used to keep something secure</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:17\">DAN 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:34\">DEU 32:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:17\">JOB 14:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:9\">PSA 40:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:12\">SNG 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:65-Matt27:66\">MAT 27:65–27:66</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:3\">REV 20:3</a></p>\n<h2>Documents sealed to prevent alteration</h2>\n<h3>Binding agreements</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:38-Neh10:1\">NEH 9:38–10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:10-Jer32:11\">JER 32:10–32:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:14\">JER 32:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:44\">JER 32:44</a></p>\n<h3>The words of prophecy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:4\">DAN 12:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:16-Isa8:17\">ISA 8:16–8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:10-Isa29:11\">ISA 29:10–29:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:26\">DAN 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:24\">DAN 9:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:9\">DAN 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:4\">REV 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:10\">REV 22:10</a></p>\n<h3>The scroll and its seals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:1-Rev5:4\">REV 5:1–5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:5\">REV 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:1-Rev6:12\">REV 6:1–6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:1\">REV 8:1</a></p>\n<h2>A seal as a pledge or guarantee</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:12\">DEU 29:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:23\">HAG 2:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:11\">ROM 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>A seal as a mark of belonging</h2>\n<h3>The mark of the beast</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:16-Rev13:17\">REV 13:16–13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:9-Rev14:11\">REV 14:9–14:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's seal of ownership</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:19\">2TI 2:19</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:3-Rev7:8\">REV 7:3–7:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek9:4\">EZK 9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:17\">GAL 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:4\">REV 9:4</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit as a pledge of final redemption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:21-2Cor1:22\">2CO 1:21–1:22</a></strong> <em>The Holy Spirit both seals believers as belonging to God and guarantees their future inheritance.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a></p>",
